1
00:00:54,013 --> 00:00:54,747
(This drama is a work of fiction.)

2
00:00:54,747 --> 00:00:55,548
(All characters, organizations,
and events in this drama are fictitious.)

3
00:00:55,548 --> 00:00:56,282
(This drama complied
with production guidelines...)

4
00:00:56,282 --> 00:00:57,016
(for filming child actors and animals.)

5
00:01:01,521 --> 00:01:02,755
What are you going to do now?

6
00:01:04,023 --> 00:01:07,059
The fact that Myo Jin
found out about the three of us...

7
00:01:07,059 --> 00:01:08,161
was not, like you thought,

8
00:01:08,995 --> 00:01:11,998
something that just
came back to her naturally over time.

9
00:01:13,833 --> 00:01:14,967
That doesn't make sense.

10
00:01:16,335 --> 00:01:17,837
She went around looking everywhere,

11
00:01:19,205 --> 00:01:21,674
meeting people, and learned it that way.

12
00:01:24,277 --> 00:01:26,879
I didn't think
she'd find out this quickly.

13
00:01:27,947 --> 00:01:28,848
What matters is...

14
00:01:29,949 --> 00:01:32,251
she's not going to sit still
from here on out.

15
00:01:36,055 --> 00:01:36,889
Then,

16
00:01:37,890 --> 00:01:39,225
what am I supposed to do?

17
00:01:40,193 --> 00:01:41,093
Stop her.

18
00:01:41,994 --> 00:01:42,829
Do you think...

19
00:01:43,896 --> 00:01:44,831
that'll be possible?

20
00:01:47,366 --> 00:01:49,836
Do you think you can afford
to be thinking like that right now?

21
00:01:50,670 --> 00:01:51,838
If this goes any further,

22
00:01:52,238 --> 00:01:54,240
have you imagined what will happen to us?

23
00:01:56,075 --> 00:01:57,510
You can't let it go any further.

24
00:01:58,878 --> 00:02:00,146
You have no choice.

25
00:02:00,546 --> 00:02:01,814
Protecting Myo Jin...

26
00:02:03,082 --> 00:02:04,183
means protecting everyone.

27
00:02:07,587 --> 00:02:08,855
You look like you're hesitating.

28
00:02:10,323 --> 00:02:11,224
Why?

29
00:02:11,824 --> 00:02:12,792
You're not confident?

30
00:02:14,527 --> 00:02:18,030
Then should we just give up on everything?

31
00:02:18,030 --> 00:02:18,931
Shut up!

32
00:02:50,897 --> 00:02:52,565
You don't care that the chairman died,

33
00:02:52,999 --> 00:02:55,101
and you just want to grab
what you can and run?

34
00:02:55,101 --> 00:02:56,002
Is that it?

35
00:02:56,002 --> 00:02:57,804
Do you think I don't know
what you're really after?

36
00:02:58,437 --> 00:02:59,872
I will expose
the one who did that to the chairman...

37
00:03:00,439 --> 00:03:01,707
soon enough.

38
00:03:01,707 --> 00:03:04,477
If the police can't,
I'll expose him myself.

39
00:03:04,677 --> 00:03:06,212
I think I know who it is.

40
00:03:06,679 --> 00:03:07,980
You bastard.

41
00:03:21,994 --> 00:03:25,364
(Caught)

42
00:03:26,432 --> 00:03:27,300
Yeah.

43
00:03:27,667 --> 00:03:28,634
Yeah, I know.

44
00:03:29,235 --> 00:03:31,170
We just need to watch a little longer.

45
00:03:31,838 --> 00:03:34,507
Yeah, I'd appreciate that.

46
00:03:40,112 --> 00:03:41,347
It's a relief.

47
00:03:41,347 --> 00:03:42,582
He's in the ICU right now,

48
00:03:42,582 --> 00:03:43,950
but they say he'll live.

49
00:03:47,153 --> 00:03:49,455
But are you okay?

50
00:03:52,124 --> 00:03:54,427
He beat me even after I said I was a cop.

51
00:03:56,028 --> 00:03:57,530
Just let him wake up.

52
00:03:58,197 --> 00:03:59,866
I'll put him right back in the hospital.

53
00:04:02,535 --> 00:04:05,471
Anyway, business is business. Let's see.

54
00:04:05,705 --> 00:04:06,706
The copy worked fine, right?

55
00:04:08,741 --> 00:04:10,143
- Here.
- Okay.

56
00:04:10,143 --> 00:04:13,279
I planned it all out in advance,

57
00:04:13,913 --> 00:04:15,815
so that should've been plenty of time.

58
00:04:16,349 --> 00:04:17,950
Let's check it first.

59
00:04:18,718 --> 00:04:21,053
All you need to check
in someone's phone...

60
00:04:21,621 --> 00:04:22,722
is the texts.

61
00:04:23,523 --> 00:04:24,624
Her name was Hee Su, right?

62
00:04:24,924 --> 00:04:26,359
Yes. Choi Hee Su.

63
00:04:26,359 --> 00:04:28,694
Once we check
what messages they exchanged,

64
00:04:28,694 --> 00:04:30,196
the answer will be clear.

65
00:04:30,429 --> 00:04:33,800
The answer to
what she was trying so hard to hide,

66
00:04:34,133 --> 00:04:36,068
and how you are connected to all this.

67
00:04:36,969 --> 00:04:38,704
Choi Hee Su.

68
00:04:39,005 --> 00:04:39,939
Choi Hee Su.

69
00:04:41,040 --> 00:04:42,475
Choi Hee Su.

70
00:04:42,475 --> 00:04:43,276
There!

71
00:04:43,643 --> 00:04:44,811
Here's Choi Hee Su.

72
00:04:45,912 --> 00:04:47,713
Yes.

73
00:04:48,414 --> 00:04:50,650
So she really was being blackmailed.

74
00:04:51,484 --> 00:04:52,852
But all this says...

75
00:04:53,586 --> 00:04:55,388
is to do exactly what he says.

76
00:04:55,888 --> 00:04:57,824
Usually, people ask for money.

77
00:04:57,824 --> 00:04:58,825
There.

78
00:04:59,425 --> 00:05:01,460
From here on,
Lee Jong Su's name keeps coming up.

79
00:05:01,928 --> 00:05:03,029
Let's see.

80
00:05:03,029 --> 00:05:04,163
Yes!

81
00:05:04,864 --> 00:05:06,466
I knew it.

82
00:05:06,999 --> 00:05:07,834
What? 300,000 dollars?

83
00:05:08,701 --> 00:05:09,669
At once?

84
00:05:10,837 --> 00:05:11,737
What?

85
00:05:11,737 --> 00:05:13,573
Whatever he had on her, it was serious.

86
00:05:13,573 --> 00:05:14,507
It had to be.

87
00:05:14,774 --> 00:05:16,275
- Scroll down more.
- Okay.

88
00:05:17,143 --> 00:05:20,179
Even after getting the money,
he kept threatening her.

89
00:05:20,179 --> 00:05:21,714
What's this?

90
00:05:22,548 --> 00:05:25,618
But here, he's sending pictures of a man.

91
00:05:26,252 --> 00:05:27,453
Was this blackmail too?

92
00:05:30,056 --> 00:05:30,890
This...

93
00:05:31,858 --> 00:05:33,092
This is...

94
00:05:33,092 --> 00:05:33,960
But...

95
00:05:34,327 --> 00:05:36,028
Why...

96
00:05:40,433 --> 00:05:41,267
This...

97
00:05:42,635 --> 00:05:43,836
This...

98
00:05:43,836 --> 00:05:45,238
So that's what it was?

99
00:05:57,850 --> 00:05:59,385
They'll care a lot about this.

100
00:05:59,652 --> 00:06:02,188
I put a little pressure on them...

101
00:06:02,188 --> 00:06:03,556
because it's my only daughter's gallery.

102
00:06:04,590 --> 00:06:07,193
You're a five-term lawmaker
up for re-election.

103
00:06:07,760 --> 00:06:08,995
So I'm sure they'll do a good job.

104
00:06:10,429 --> 00:06:13,499
But among the merchants
who hover around politicians,

105
00:06:14,167 --> 00:06:15,668
there aren't many decent ones.

106
00:06:16,335 --> 00:06:18,571
"Merchants?"

107
00:06:18,571 --> 00:06:21,407
He's top-level in Korean architecture.

108
00:06:22,708 --> 00:06:24,744
I don't know how close you are,

109
00:06:25,745 --> 00:06:27,280
but is it okay to ask a favor like this?

110
00:06:28,447 --> 00:06:30,316
The construction costs must be enormous.

111
00:06:31,184 --> 00:06:33,319
I'll handle it.

112
00:06:35,421 --> 00:06:36,222
What a surprise.

113
00:06:36,856 --> 00:06:39,192
What brings you here
all of a sudden, Mr. Cho?

114
00:06:40,226 --> 00:06:42,195
Something urgent came up
that I needed to discuss,

115
00:06:42,195 --> 00:06:43,996
and I heard you were here, sir.

116
00:06:44,263 --> 00:06:45,131
I see.

117
00:06:45,431 --> 00:06:46,299
Take a seat.

118
00:06:52,605 --> 00:06:54,407
What is it you wanted to discuss?

119
00:06:54,407 --> 00:06:55,541
It's just that,

120
00:06:56,175 --> 00:06:58,544
as you said, CEO Oh Sang Il seems...

121
00:06:58,544 --> 00:07:00,513
to have actually met with Ryu Jun Ho.

122
00:07:00,980 --> 00:07:04,350
So that Ryu Jun Ho really did
crawl in through a back door.

123
00:07:04,884 --> 00:07:08,254
It's something I could laugh off myself,

124
00:07:08,554 --> 00:07:11,290
but if word of this somehow gets out,

125
00:07:12,225 --> 00:07:14,227
the image of the competition hosts...

126
00:07:18,397 --> 00:07:19,432
But...

127
00:07:20,032 --> 00:07:22,235
isn't your information a little late?

128
00:07:22,702 --> 00:07:23,636
Pardon?

129
00:07:23,636 --> 00:07:25,438
Yesterday,

130
00:07:25,438 --> 00:07:27,507
the organizers
apparently held discussions...

131
00:07:27,507 --> 00:07:31,277
about new internal rules
related to this competition.

132
00:07:32,845 --> 00:07:35,448
It seems to have happened
at CEO Oh's strong request.

133
00:07:37,083 --> 00:07:40,753
Wouldn't it be more urgent
to find out what that is?

134
00:07:47,693 --> 00:07:49,028
People...

135
00:07:49,028 --> 00:07:50,396
make mistakes sometimes,

136
00:07:50,930 --> 00:07:52,799
and get shaken down too.

137
00:07:53,299 --> 00:07:55,568
That's what happens
when you get caught in a love triangle.

138
00:07:55,568 --> 00:07:57,837
Well, spilled water is spilled water.

139
00:07:57,837 --> 00:08:00,339
You wipe it clean
and make sure it doesn't happen again.

140
00:08:04,477 --> 00:08:06,212
There's this saying.

141
00:08:06,813 --> 00:08:09,081
Even if you get hit by the first arrow,
don't get hit by the second.

142
00:08:09,282 --> 00:08:12,285
Don't beat yourself up
over something that's already...

143
00:08:12,285 --> 00:08:13,519
- Lee Jong Su.
- You startled me.

144
00:08:13,519 --> 00:08:14,854
Why was he tormenting Hee Su?

145
00:08:15,188 --> 00:08:17,190
Isn't it obvious? For money.

146
00:08:17,190 --> 00:08:19,392
You saw it.
He extorted 300,000 in one shot.

147
00:08:19,826 --> 00:08:20,693
No.

148
00:08:21,294 --> 00:08:22,261
It wasn't about money.

149
00:08:22,461 --> 00:08:23,396
It wasn't?

150
00:08:23,396 --> 00:08:24,764
Hee Su was the victim.

151
00:08:25,498 --> 00:08:26,632
With those photos,

152
00:08:26,632 --> 00:08:28,367
the people he should've
been threatening...

153
00:08:28,367 --> 00:08:30,736
weren't Hee Su, but Ryu Jun Ho and me.

154
00:08:31,003 --> 00:08:32,605
If money was the goal,
that's what makes sense.

155
00:08:33,506 --> 00:08:34,373
Is that so?

156
00:08:35,708 --> 00:08:37,510
Lee Jong Su had another reason.

157
00:08:38,244 --> 00:08:39,745
And Hee Su was afraid of that.

158
00:08:41,247 --> 00:08:42,748
Something that hurt Hee Su...

159
00:08:44,350 --> 00:08:46,219
more than my relationship with Ryu Jun Ho.

160
00:09:08,875 --> 00:09:09,709
Here.

161
00:09:12,912 --> 00:09:14,380
Hamburgers.

162
00:09:15,081 --> 00:09:17,116
It's late, so go inside.

163
00:09:18,017 --> 00:09:19,352
Leave one for your brother.

164
00:09:24,490 --> 00:09:25,358
Sir.

165
00:09:26,225 --> 00:09:27,093
Yeah?

166
00:09:27,460 --> 00:09:29,262
Are you rich?

167
00:09:30,029 --> 00:09:30,863
Rich?

168
00:09:30,863 --> 00:09:31,731
Yes.

169
00:09:33,399 --> 00:09:34,233
Sure.

170
00:09:34,667 --> 00:09:35,535
I'm rich.

171
00:09:36,235 --> 00:09:37,637
How rich?

172
00:09:38,604 --> 00:09:39,972
Rich enough...

173
00:09:40,873 --> 00:09:42,441
to buy you that bread every single day.

174
00:09:43,075 --> 00:09:43,910
Cool.

175
00:09:45,745 --> 00:09:48,681
But where did all your money come from?

176
00:09:50,416 --> 00:09:51,551
How...

177
00:09:51,551 --> 00:09:53,719
do I get rich like you?

178
00:10:20,580 --> 00:10:21,547
Who are you people?

179
00:10:24,217 --> 00:10:24,984
Answer me.

180
00:10:57,817 --> 00:10:58,684
Hey.

181
00:11:00,753 --> 00:11:02,221
Stop this.

182
00:11:02,588 --> 00:11:04,157
This is too much.

183
00:11:04,157 --> 00:11:06,459
Why are you doing this
like a bunch of idiots?

184
00:11:07,360 --> 00:11:08,928
Have some common sense.

185
00:11:09,896 --> 00:11:11,464
At this point,

186
00:11:11,464 --> 00:11:12,932
he should have figured it out...

187
00:11:14,734 --> 00:11:16,235
since he's smart and quick on the uptake.

188
00:11:17,270 --> 00:11:18,404
Mr. Ryu.

189
00:11:23,442 --> 00:11:24,644
Isn't that right?

190
00:11:25,678 --> 00:11:28,447
CEO Ryu Jun Ho of Mono Architecture.

191
00:11:35,721 --> 00:11:37,223
Did your heart skip a beat?

192
00:11:38,491 --> 00:11:40,326
Did you think if you pulled strings
behind the scenes,

193
00:11:40,893 --> 00:11:42,295
no one would know?

194
00:11:43,095 --> 00:11:45,364
When the stench is this thick everywhere?

195
00:11:47,567 --> 00:11:49,569
Stay out of this competition.

196
00:11:50,803 --> 00:11:52,238
Today's just a warning.

197
00:11:52,872 --> 00:11:55,274
If I hear your name again,

198
00:11:55,942 --> 00:11:56,843
then,

199
00:11:58,744 --> 00:12:00,913
even that handsome face I spared today...

200
00:12:03,883 --> 00:12:05,451
won't survive.

201
00:12:10,022 --> 00:12:11,123
Let's go.

202
00:12:21,200 --> 00:12:23,669
Hey, long time no see.

203
00:12:23,669 --> 00:12:24,504
Yes.

204
00:12:25,304 --> 00:12:26,639
You eat well.

205
00:12:26,639 --> 00:12:28,574
Two servings are gone just like that.

206
00:12:30,877 --> 00:12:33,980
But is it really that important
to know where Detective Kang is?

207
00:12:33,980 --> 00:12:35,348
No way.

208
00:12:35,348 --> 00:12:36,883
I can easily find out.

209
00:12:37,750 --> 00:12:38,951
Then why...

210
00:12:38,951 --> 00:12:41,187
I'm just grateful, that's all.

211
00:12:42,488 --> 00:12:43,523
Because from here on,

212
00:12:44,090 --> 00:12:45,558
there's something I need you to tell me.

213
00:12:46,759 --> 00:12:47,627
Sorry?

214
00:12:47,894 --> 00:12:49,195
Something happened
to Detective Kang, right?

215
00:12:49,495 --> 00:12:51,664
He didn't just step away
from the villa case, right?

216
00:12:56,402 --> 00:12:57,403
How would I know?

217
00:12:58,037 --> 00:12:58,838
Hey.

218
00:12:59,505 --> 00:13:00,706
When you got here,

219
00:13:00,706 --> 00:13:02,408
it was Detective Kang
who taught you everything, right?

220
00:13:02,875 --> 00:13:03,776
I...

221
00:13:04,944 --> 00:13:07,113
practically raised Detective Kang
from diapers.

222
00:13:11,851 --> 00:13:13,619
Before Detective Kang quit,

223
00:13:14,253 --> 00:13:16,022
you two drank together
every night for a month.

224
00:13:16,689 --> 00:13:17,857
What did the two of you talk about?

225
00:13:18,558 --> 00:13:21,460
If I say the wrong thing
and something blows up...

226
00:13:22,328 --> 00:13:23,696
Hey, look at me.

227
00:13:25,965 --> 00:13:27,366
I need your help.

228
00:13:27,900 --> 00:13:30,069
We have to bring
Detective Kang back, don't we?

229
00:13:38,010 --> 00:13:40,980
Detective Kang didn't just quit.

230
00:13:41,747 --> 00:13:44,784
Every time we drank,
he kept saying he couldn't trust anyone.

231
00:13:46,185 --> 00:13:47,987
He said he found out something important,

232
00:13:47,987 --> 00:13:50,289
but that he couldn't step in right now.

233
00:13:50,289 --> 00:13:51,157
What was it?

234
00:13:51,157 --> 00:13:52,225
I really don't know that.

235
00:13:55,094 --> 00:13:57,096
He just said...

236
00:13:57,096 --> 00:13:59,499
he'd rather take it to the grave
than let it out halfway.

237
00:14:21,320 --> 00:14:22,188
That's empty.

238
00:14:51,317 --> 00:14:52,418
Were you watching me?

239
00:14:53,052 --> 00:14:54,453
You looked troubled.

240
00:14:56,022 --> 00:14:57,723
I had some thinking to do too.

241
00:15:01,894 --> 00:15:04,230
On sports day back in elementary school,

242
00:15:04,230 --> 00:15:06,599
there was this event
called Find-a-Person Race.

243
00:15:07,934 --> 00:15:09,635
I loved it...

244
00:15:11,270 --> 00:15:13,072
because I was confident about running.

245
00:15:15,441 --> 00:15:17,643
When it was my turn,

246
00:15:17,643 --> 00:15:19,946
I picked a slip of paper,

247
00:15:19,946 --> 00:15:20,847
and on it...

248
00:15:22,515 --> 00:15:24,050
was written, "Mom."

249
00:15:26,786 --> 00:15:29,188
The person who wrote that
would never have known...

250
00:15:30,056 --> 00:15:30,923
that...

251
00:15:32,291 --> 00:15:36,462
a kid without a mother
would be the one to pick it.

252
00:15:39,765 --> 00:15:40,666
Back then,

253
00:15:41,267 --> 00:15:43,769
I think I realized something.

254
00:15:45,638 --> 00:15:46,806
Rules...

255
00:15:48,774 --> 00:15:50,743
aren't made...

256
00:15:52,378 --> 00:15:55,081
for the people without,
but for the people with.

257
00:16:01,087 --> 00:16:04,123
I think it was around then...

258
00:16:05,691 --> 00:16:08,861
that I learned my mom and dad
had died in an accident,

259
00:16:10,496 --> 00:16:11,931
not gone to America to make money.

260
00:16:15,568 --> 00:16:18,571
I begged my grandmother for days...

261
00:16:20,106 --> 00:16:21,073
to tell me the truth.

262
00:16:21,607 --> 00:16:23,843
So what did you do?

263
00:16:26,179 --> 00:16:28,681
I just grabbed the hand
of a woman who looked like a mom and ran.

264
00:16:30,483 --> 00:16:31,684
With the whole school watching,

265
00:16:32,919 --> 00:16:35,855
I didn't want anyone to know
I didn't have a mother.

266
00:16:45,498 --> 00:16:48,434
A man named Mr. Cho
came to see my father today,

267
00:16:49,902 --> 00:16:51,370
and I heard him talking about you.

268
00:16:56,209 --> 00:16:57,210
It was him, wasn't it?

269
00:17:00,246 --> 00:17:01,514
Thanks to that, it all clicked.

270
00:17:03,282 --> 00:17:06,252
I now know what was happening...

271
00:17:08,154 --> 00:17:09,121
without me knowing.

272
00:17:21,901 --> 00:17:22,768
I'm curious...

273
00:17:23,169 --> 00:17:24,170
about that race that day.

274
00:17:31,944 --> 00:17:33,880
I ran like crazy and came in first.

275
00:17:35,915 --> 00:17:37,183
I didn't want to lose...

276
00:17:38,251 --> 00:17:39,418
in that situation.

277
