551
00:30:41,534 --> 00:30:43,402
At two hundred each,
plus whatever extras we tack on,

552
00:30:43,402 --> 00:30:44,670
do you know how much that is?

553
00:30:44,670 --> 00:30:45,805
It's a total jackpot, right?

554
00:30:46,506 --> 00:30:48,141
What date is it?

555
00:30:48,141 --> 00:30:49,442
It's 8 p.m. the day after tomorrow.

556
00:30:49,442 --> 00:30:50,943
Damn it, then that won't work.

557
00:30:50,943 --> 00:30:52,478
I've got something
I need to finish that day.

558
00:30:53,045 --> 00:30:55,047
- Call me next time. I'm hanging up.
- Wait, Mr. Ahn.

559
00:30:55,047 --> 00:30:56,949
Would next week work?

560
00:30:56,949 --> 00:30:58,050
There's an important gathering.

561
00:30:58,050 --> 00:30:59,952
There'll be about 50 people, so it's easy.

562
00:30:59,952 --> 00:31:00,853
Wait a second.

563
00:31:00,853 --> 00:31:02,088
What was the date again? Hold on.

564
00:31:02,088 --> 00:31:03,890
What are you talking about?
Hang up. I'm busy.

565
00:31:03,890 --> 00:31:05,591
Hey, you bastard, do as you're told.

566
00:31:05,591 --> 00:31:07,660
What kind of work
could a bastard like you possibly have?

567
00:31:07,660 --> 00:31:10,229
Fuck, please don't hang up.

568
00:31:10,229 --> 00:31:11,164
(Tracking location)

569
00:31:12,131 --> 00:31:13,232
What a psycho.

570
00:31:14,267 --> 00:31:15,168
Boss.

571
00:31:15,168 --> 00:31:16,202
We got him.

572
00:31:20,106 --> 00:31:21,073
Have a drink.

573
00:31:24,777 --> 00:31:27,847
(Mono)

574
00:31:43,396 --> 00:31:44,797
What you're saying is correct, sir.

575
00:31:45,398 --> 00:31:48,034
It's true that you achieved the results
within the promised period,

576
00:31:48,601 --> 00:31:49,769
and your request to separate
from headquarters...

577
00:31:50,937 --> 00:31:52,572
is justified, I believe.

578
00:31:53,840 --> 00:31:55,074
The vice chairman said...

579
00:31:55,741 --> 00:31:59,245
the person making the biggest issue out of
separating my company from headquarters...

580
00:32:00,046 --> 00:32:01,814
is you, the head of legal.

581
00:32:02,081 --> 00:32:04,016
Yes, that's right.

582
00:32:04,016 --> 00:32:05,117
And why is that?

583
00:32:05,451 --> 00:32:07,453
Because of Article 19...

584
00:32:07,453 --> 00:32:09,288
of the Mono Group bylaws, Clause Three.

585
00:32:10,056 --> 00:32:12,291
In the event of force majeure,

586
00:32:12,291 --> 00:32:13,659
company decision-making...

587
00:32:14,227 --> 00:32:17,096
must follow the decision
of the top executive.

588
00:32:17,997 --> 00:32:19,198
As you know,

589
00:32:19,198 --> 00:32:21,701
the vice chairman is temporarily
filling that role right now.

590
00:32:22,335 --> 00:32:24,270
So please understand
that we can't really do anything...

591
00:32:24,270 --> 00:32:26,272
about a matter the vice chairman opposes.

592
00:32:30,076 --> 00:32:32,912
Board Operations Regulation,
Article Five, Clause One.

593
00:32:32,912 --> 00:32:34,647
If the representative director is absent,

594
00:32:34,647 --> 00:32:37,517
a new person must be elected
through the board...

595
00:32:37,517 --> 00:32:39,752
within 60 days at most.

596
00:32:40,119 --> 00:32:42,054
But the date specified in the bylaws...

597
00:32:42,054 --> 00:32:43,322
has already passed.

598
00:32:44,790 --> 00:32:46,425
Calling that board meeting...

599
00:32:46,425 --> 00:32:48,361
isn't difficult in itself,

600
00:32:48,361 --> 00:32:51,063
but because careful consideration
takes time in choosing the right person,

601
00:32:51,063 --> 00:32:53,566
it would be hard to claim
that it's illegal.

602
00:32:54,000 --> 00:32:55,268
I'm sorry,

603
00:32:55,268 --> 00:32:56,602
but please wait just a little longer.

604
00:32:56,602 --> 00:32:59,705
It sounds like there's another reason
besides what you're saying.

605
00:33:21,327 --> 00:33:23,563
Would it be all right...

606
00:33:24,130 --> 00:33:25,364
if I spoke a little more frankly?

607
00:33:25,665 --> 00:33:26,933
Of course.

608
00:33:26,933 --> 00:33:27,767
Sir,

609
00:33:27,767 --> 00:33:30,436
there's no other way.
You should just file suit.

610
00:33:31,771 --> 00:33:33,706
The vice chairman won't listen to reason.

611
00:33:34,373 --> 00:33:36,309
Even when I tell him to start
by getting board approval,

612
00:33:36,309 --> 00:33:37,810
he shuts down completely.

613
00:33:39,312 --> 00:33:40,746
Even when I tell him
that if he keeps doing this,

614
00:33:40,746 --> 00:33:42,348
he'll have no choice
but to accept your demands,

615
00:33:42,348 --> 00:33:43,449
no matter how much
I try to persuade him...

616
00:33:43,449 --> 00:33:45,818
You must have had a hard time, sir.

617
00:33:48,788 --> 00:33:51,858
Problems between people
are all about emotion in the end,

618
00:33:51,858 --> 00:33:52,925
not logic.

619
00:33:53,259 --> 00:33:55,628
The vice chairman isn't going
to change going forward either.

620
00:33:57,430 --> 00:33:59,265
I've done everything I can,

621
00:34:00,133 --> 00:34:01,134
but it's not enough.

622
00:34:04,036 --> 00:34:06,105
All right, I've heard your proposal.

623
00:34:06,105 --> 00:34:07,507
Let's leave it here for today.

624
00:34:08,341 --> 00:34:09,809
Let's do that.

625
00:34:12,211 --> 00:34:13,179
Understood.

626
00:34:18,417 --> 00:34:19,485
Just keep looking ahead.

627
00:34:20,219 --> 00:34:21,687
He's probably trying to push you
into a lawsuit.

628
00:34:22,088 --> 00:34:24,323
He'd drag it out all the way
to a Supreme Court ruling,

629
00:34:24,323 --> 00:34:25,758
and expose every side of you...

630
00:34:25,758 --> 00:34:27,426
the public doesn't know. That's his goal.

631
00:34:28,094 --> 00:34:29,962
He'll keep provoking you.

632
00:34:29,962 --> 00:34:31,831
Is that the man Chief Kim mentioned?

633
00:34:31,831 --> 00:34:34,267
It seems he called in the head of legal
and gave him orders yesterday.

634
00:34:36,035 --> 00:34:38,204
If he hates me that much, what can I do?

635
00:34:38,204 --> 00:34:39,505
I have to give him what he wants.

636
00:34:40,606 --> 00:34:42,875
It was the first favor
that thoughtful friend ever asked.

637
00:34:42,875 --> 00:34:44,043
I fell short in many ways.

638
00:34:44,043 --> 00:34:45,578
No, it was enough.

639
00:34:45,578 --> 00:34:46,612
Thank you.

640
00:34:47,046 --> 00:34:48,881
You should check
your online accounts often too.

641
00:34:49,215 --> 00:34:51,083
There's a junior of his in IT...

642
00:34:51,384 --> 00:34:53,586
who's a total lunatic
and loves cracking hard passwords.

643
00:35:01,594 --> 00:35:03,062
What do you think you've got...

644
00:35:03,062 --> 00:35:05,665
to keep holding out for?

645
00:35:05,665 --> 00:35:07,834
You've got a lot of nerve.

646
00:35:07,834 --> 00:35:08,801
All right.

647
00:35:09,235 --> 00:35:11,537
All right, so please.

648
00:35:11,537 --> 00:35:13,206
If you were going to learn anyway,

649
00:35:13,206 --> 00:35:15,308
why learn it only now?

650
00:35:15,308 --> 00:35:16,742
If you'd learned before I came,

651
00:35:16,742 --> 00:35:19,278
how much better that would have been.

652
00:35:19,278 --> 00:35:20,546
I'm leaving...

653
00:35:20,546 --> 00:35:21,981
tomorrow first thing.

654
00:35:21,981 --> 00:35:22,882
Come out.

655
00:35:22,882 --> 00:35:24,150
- What are you doing?
- I said come out.

656
00:35:26,419 --> 00:35:29,188
No, you don't have to go anywhere.

657
00:35:29,188 --> 00:35:32,024
You all stay right where you are too.

658
00:35:32,358 --> 00:35:34,660
I'm stopping the demolition here today.

659
00:35:35,294 --> 00:35:37,663
Let's live seeing my face every day.

660
00:35:38,464 --> 00:35:40,500
Hey, how nice is that?

661
00:35:40,500 --> 00:35:43,469
There are plenty
of people here too, right?

662
00:35:45,271 --> 00:35:46,739
For a hundred years, a thousand years,

663
00:35:46,739 --> 00:35:49,242
keep doing business here...

664
00:35:50,076 --> 00:35:51,277
day in, day out.

665
00:35:54,914 --> 00:35:56,415
You little punks.

666
00:35:57,450 --> 00:35:59,385
What kind of stunt is this
in broad daylight?

667
00:36:01,320 --> 00:36:03,890
It seems we've got someone new...

668
00:36:03,890 --> 00:36:05,124
after a long time.

669
00:36:07,293 --> 00:36:08,127
What?

670
00:36:08,694 --> 00:36:09,629
Gi Cheol?

671
00:36:16,769 --> 00:36:20,039
I heard you made money,

672
00:36:20,840 --> 00:36:23,309
but I didn't know
you were holding out here too.

673
00:36:23,709 --> 00:36:25,645
Holding out? No.

674
00:36:25,845 --> 00:36:28,481
Come on,
the compensation must be pretty good.

675
00:36:28,915 --> 00:36:30,917
It must be nice for you.
You're making money.

676
00:36:31,918 --> 00:36:33,986
Stop harassing these people
and leave them alone.

677
00:36:34,754 --> 00:36:36,589
They're all moving out next week anyway.

678
00:36:36,589 --> 00:36:38,624
What? That soon?

679
00:36:38,624 --> 00:36:39,892
No.

680
00:36:39,892 --> 00:36:40,760
Sir.

681
00:36:40,760 --> 00:36:42,929
Tell them to hold out
just a few more days.

682
00:36:43,896 --> 00:36:46,432
They have no idea what I make in a day.
They can't end it already.

683
00:36:47,066 --> 00:36:49,869
These bastards are scared of everything.

684
00:36:51,270 --> 00:36:52,271
You psycho.

685
00:36:53,005 --> 00:36:55,107
I'm strapped for cash, sir.

686
00:36:55,708 --> 00:36:57,176
Let's stretch it out for just a few days.

687
00:36:57,577 --> 00:36:59,178
What about ten days?

688
00:36:59,612 --> 00:37:01,414
That's nonsense.

689
00:37:01,914 --> 00:37:02,849
Don't come back.

690
00:37:03,115 --> 00:37:04,317
Come on.

691
00:37:05,251 --> 00:37:07,520
We're all just trying to make a living.

692
00:37:07,520 --> 00:37:09,422
When things are rough,
we should help each other out.

693
00:37:10,256 --> 00:37:12,225
My wise prison buddy.

694
00:37:12,692 --> 00:37:14,160
Brother.

695
00:37:15,061 --> 00:37:16,195
Damn it.

696
00:37:17,997 --> 00:37:19,465
Sir.

697
00:37:20,933 --> 00:37:22,068
Hey.

698
00:37:24,770 --> 00:37:27,573
What is this, some spy movie?

699
00:37:27,573 --> 00:37:29,075
What are you doing?

700
00:37:30,376 --> 00:37:31,711
It just turned out this way.

701
00:37:31,711 --> 00:37:32,512
Have you been well?

702
00:37:32,512 --> 00:37:33,312
Yeah.

703
00:37:33,880 --> 00:37:35,715
You should've just come inside.

704
00:37:35,715 --> 00:37:36,816
Why didn't you?

705
00:37:37,383 --> 00:37:39,185
Did you commit a crime?

706
00:37:40,086 --> 00:37:41,988
There are too many ears at the station,

707
00:37:43,122 --> 00:37:44,724
and if I run into someone I know,

708
00:37:44,724 --> 00:37:46,359
it'll be, "Who came? Why'd he come?"

709
00:37:46,859 --> 00:37:48,261
I'm sick of that pointless chatter.

710
00:37:49,095 --> 00:37:51,197
All right, then spit it out.

711
00:37:51,397 --> 00:37:53,366
What is it
that's got you acting so serious?

712
00:37:53,599 --> 00:37:54,634
If it's not worth hearing,

713
00:37:54,634 --> 00:37:56,836
then you're buying lunch down there.

714
00:37:58,137 --> 00:37:59,405
Hangover soup and radish kimchi.

715
00:38:00,339 --> 00:38:01,641
Fine, I will.

716
00:38:03,176 --> 00:38:04,243
But Detective Kang,

717
00:38:05,111 --> 00:38:08,214
you handled the Jebudo Island
villa explosion case, didn't you?

718
00:38:09,015 --> 00:38:10,917
I'm the one working it now.

719
00:38:10,917 --> 00:38:12,185
My captain brought it over.

720
00:38:13,820 --> 00:38:14,654
Sir.

721
00:38:15,788 --> 00:38:17,723
If I'd thought
you were going to ask me that,

722
00:38:17,723 --> 00:38:19,058
I wouldn't have come out.

723
00:38:20,159 --> 00:38:22,695
Come on, just tell me.

724
00:38:23,095 --> 00:38:24,797
Hey, maybe other guys would,

725
00:38:24,797 --> 00:38:26,999
but you're not the type
to investigate a case this half-assed.

726
00:38:29,302 --> 00:38:30,536
So why did you this time?

727
00:38:31,671 --> 00:38:34,006
I heard Captain Son resigned
because of a chronic condition.

728
00:38:34,774 --> 00:38:36,042
Then...

729
00:38:36,042 --> 00:38:38,678
you should've at least wrapped up the case
before transferring.

730
00:38:38,678 --> 00:38:40,480
What was so urgent that you moved here?

731
00:38:42,515 --> 00:38:44,650
You're hiding something, aren't you?

732
00:38:45,084 --> 00:38:47,119
It was all complete bullshit.

733
00:38:48,821 --> 00:38:49,589
What?

734
00:38:51,257 --> 00:38:53,025
You know my captain well, don't you?

735
00:38:53,659 --> 00:38:55,628
When he takes a case,
he's sharp as a knife.

736
00:38:55,962 --> 00:38:57,497
That's what I admired about him,

737
00:38:57,497 --> 00:39:00,233
so I was turning down offers
from senior guys.

738
00:39:00,800 --> 00:39:02,201
But that wasn't it.

739
00:39:02,835 --> 00:39:05,538
It turns out
I completely misjudged the man...

740
00:39:05,538 --> 00:39:08,040
or maybe he changed for some reason.

741
00:39:16,149 --> 00:39:18,017
I mean,
he was like Cinderella or something.

742
00:39:18,651 --> 00:39:21,020
Every chance he got, he'd disappear.

743
00:39:21,454 --> 00:39:24,457
And whatever he got, he got a big one.

744
00:39:24,991 --> 00:39:26,726
I got a bad feeling right away.

745
00:39:37,103 --> 00:39:37,870
Sir.

746
00:39:40,506 --> 00:39:41,808
The captain quit.

747
00:39:42,475 --> 00:39:43,342
What?

748
00:39:43,576 --> 00:39:44,510
You didn't know?

749
00:39:47,547 --> 00:39:48,447
And guess what?

750
00:39:49,215 --> 00:39:51,551
The man who told me even
how many times he went to the bathroom...

751
00:39:51,551 --> 00:39:53,653
did all that without a single word.

752
00:39:53,653 --> 00:39:56,656
Nobody ever heard
he was sick enough to take medical leave.

753
00:39:56,923 --> 00:39:58,224
What kind of bullshit is that?

754
00:39:58,791 --> 00:40:00,126
So I got fed up,

755
00:40:00,526 --> 00:40:02,528
and walked away from it myself.

756
00:40:03,262 --> 00:40:05,798
Did you tell anyone about...

757
00:40:05,798 --> 00:40:06,666
No.

758
00:40:06,866 --> 00:40:07,867
Did you report it to your superiors?

759
00:40:08,634 --> 00:40:09,769
That's enough.

760
00:40:10,269 --> 00:40:12,538
You know full well I could never do that.

761
00:40:15,575 --> 00:40:16,409
Right now,

762
00:40:17,510 --> 00:40:20,413
there isn't a single piece of evidence
left in this case.

763
00:40:20,980 --> 00:40:22,014
And this...

764
00:40:23,115 --> 00:40:24,150
wasn't arson.

765
00:40:24,350 --> 00:40:26,118
- It wasn't?
- At the scene,

766
00:40:26,586 --> 00:40:29,288
they found a weapon
believed to have been used in the crime,

767
00:40:29,288 --> 00:40:30,690
and it's undergoing detailed forensics.

768
00:40:32,592 --> 00:40:34,026
So it's a murder case.

769
00:40:38,197 --> 00:40:40,500
That's the only evidence
I barely managed to find.

770
00:40:41,134 --> 00:40:42,168
There's nothing else.

771
00:40:43,603 --> 00:40:45,905
When you first started investigating,

772
00:40:45,905 --> 00:40:47,240
did you find anything?

773
00:40:47,240 --> 00:40:49,308
Or do you remember anything at all?

774
00:40:49,308 --> 00:40:51,811
I walked away from all of it.
What would I know?

775
00:40:51,811 --> 00:40:54,347
It'd be quicker to ask Captain Son.

776
00:40:54,347 --> 00:40:57,283
Even if he knows, he'll say he doesn't.

777
00:40:57,283 --> 00:40:58,885
Don't do this.

778
00:40:59,152 --> 00:40:59,952
Hey!

779
00:40:59,952 --> 00:41:02,355
Do you think I'd have come
all the way here if I weren't desperate?

780
00:41:03,589 --> 00:41:05,091
I was surprised too.

781
00:41:05,558 --> 00:41:07,393
If some junior of yours
had gone off and died...

782
00:41:07,393 --> 00:41:10,363
and gotten buried somewhere,
you probably wouldn't even know.

783
00:41:12,465 --> 00:41:13,266
Hey!

784
00:41:13,666 --> 00:41:14,834
Are you really doing this?

785
00:41:15,501 --> 00:41:18,204
When you finally moved into a lease place
from a monthly rental last year,

786
00:41:18,204 --> 00:41:19,906
who lent you the money?

787
00:41:19,906 --> 00:41:21,307
And without interest too.

788
00:41:21,307 --> 00:41:22,942
Seriously?

789
00:41:22,942 --> 00:41:23,876
I'll pay you back.

790
00:41:23,876 --> 00:41:26,579
Then what were you doing
that you're only showing up now?

791
00:41:26,579 --> 00:41:29,215
Even if we're on different teams,
if you cared at all,

792
00:41:29,215 --> 00:41:31,117
how did you not know
I was suffering like that?

793
00:41:31,651 --> 00:41:32,985
What, were you dating or something?

794
00:41:33,786 --> 00:41:34,720
What?

795
00:41:36,155 --> 00:41:38,057
You know well I'm not some half-assed cop,

796
00:41:38,558 --> 00:41:40,426
and now you're showing up asking me?

797
00:41:41,794 --> 00:41:42,595
Detective Kang.

798
00:41:43,229 --> 00:41:44,096
Did you maybe...

799
00:41:45,097 --> 00:41:47,567
The villa CCTV hard drive...

800
00:41:48,701 --> 00:41:50,269
didn't burn up and disappear.

801
00:41:51,070 --> 00:41:52,438
It was taken out beforehand.

802
00:41:53,973 --> 00:41:54,907
Taken out?

803
00:41:54,907 --> 00:41:55,741
By who?

804
00:41:56,142 --> 00:41:58,311
Good grief.

805
00:41:59,111 --> 00:42:00,580
Have you really lost your touch?

806
00:42:02,448 --> 00:42:05,151
Out of those four people, two are dead,

807
00:42:06,018 --> 00:42:07,487
so aren't there only two left?

808
00:42:08,354 --> 00:42:10,456
Do you really have to experience more
to know what's behind it?

809
00:42:12,725 --> 00:42:14,093
It's obvious.

810
00:42:18,064 --> 00:42:20,233
(Wang Gi Cheol)

811
00:42:54,967 --> 00:42:56,002
Hello?

812
00:43:00,940 --> 00:43:03,009
My name is Ham Myo Jin.

813
00:43:06,179 --> 00:43:07,013
Hello?

814
00:43:14,053 --> 00:43:15,154
How have you been?

815
00:43:16,355 --> 00:43:17,156
Pardon?

816
00:43:17,924 --> 00:43:19,325
When I heard about your accident,

817
00:43:21,160 --> 00:43:22,195
I was worried.

818
00:43:22,728 --> 00:43:23,596
Do you...

819
00:43:24,263 --> 00:43:25,598
know me well?

820
00:43:27,266 --> 00:43:28,868
Because of the shock from the accident,

821
00:43:28,868 --> 00:43:30,169
I lost my memory.

822
00:43:31,037 --> 00:43:33,706
I'm recovering now,
but I still can't remember much.

823
00:43:34,740 --> 00:43:37,043
Then how did you know to call?

824
00:43:37,410 --> 00:43:39,378
I found the phone I'd lost,

825
00:43:39,712 --> 00:43:41,247
and saw the text messages and called.

826
00:43:42,181 --> 00:43:43,516
We used to keep in touch a lot,

827
00:43:43,516 --> 00:43:45,084
so I thought you might be able to help me.

828
00:43:45,685 --> 00:43:46,586
Interesting.

829
00:43:47,453 --> 00:43:49,822
So you've gone all the way
back to the beginning?

830
00:43:50,690 --> 00:43:51,524
Pardon?

831
00:43:52,024 --> 00:43:53,326
You mean you don't even remember...

832
00:43:54,694 --> 00:43:56,762
who I am now, right?

833
00:44:00,399 --> 00:44:01,501
Please tell me.

834
00:44:02,135 --> 00:44:03,603
How do I know you?

835
00:44:05,171 --> 00:44:06,472
You don't need to be curious.

836
00:44:07,640 --> 00:44:09,575
If you know, it puts us both in danger.

837
00:44:09,575 --> 00:44:12,278
Hang up this call and delete my number.

838
00:44:12,712 --> 00:44:14,514
Not that I'd answer again anyway.

839
00:44:14,514 --> 00:44:15,882
I met Lee Jong Su.

840
00:44:16,782 --> 00:44:18,251
He had an accident.

841
00:44:19,051 --> 00:44:20,319
He's in the hospital right now.

842
00:44:23,456 --> 00:44:24,524
Hello?

843
00:44:25,324 --> 00:44:26,192
Who did it?

844
00:44:27,360 --> 00:44:28,194
What?

845
00:44:28,394 --> 00:44:30,196
Who did that to him?

846
00:44:31,631 --> 00:44:32,532
Don't tell me...

847
00:44:33,533 --> 00:44:34,567
it was you.

848
00:44:36,536 --> 00:44:37,937
I'll tell you in person.

849
00:44:38,938 --> 00:44:39,839
Everything.

850
00:44:42,375 --> 00:44:47,446
(Redevelopment has us furious.
We oppose it again and again.)

851
00:45:13,172 --> 00:45:17,944
(Star Karaoke Bar)

852
00:45:58,651 --> 00:45:59,952
Why did you come back?

853
00:46:08,261 --> 00:46:10,096
Go ahead, bastard.

854
00:46:11,931 --> 00:46:13,132
I warned you.

855
00:46:13,132 --> 00:46:15,067
Nothing good comes from us meeting.

856
00:46:15,535 --> 00:46:16,536
I just...

857
00:46:17,737 --> 00:46:19,438
want my memory back.

858
00:46:19,972 --> 00:46:21,207
That's why I came here.

859
00:46:21,641 --> 00:46:23,342
What happened to Jong Su?

860
00:46:23,342 --> 00:46:25,478
I found out
he had been blackmailing my friend,

861
00:46:25,478 --> 00:46:26,779
so I went to see him.

862
00:46:27,113 --> 00:46:28,781
To ask what had happened.

863
00:46:38,758 --> 00:46:40,326
But Choi Hee Su is dead.

864
00:46:41,661 --> 00:46:42,929
You know Hee Su?

865
00:46:43,429 --> 00:46:44,430
How do you know her?

866
00:46:45,097 --> 00:46:46,532
What are you to her?

867
00:46:46,532 --> 00:46:47,800
When I stopped hearing from you,

868
00:46:50,203 --> 00:46:52,939
I thought you'd forgotten everything
and started over.

869
00:46:52,939 --> 00:46:53,940
Please.

870
00:46:54,807 --> 00:46:56,476
Tell me what you know about me.

871
00:47:16,362 --> 00:47:17,230
You.

872
00:47:18,931 --> 00:47:19,765
How much...

873
00:47:20,366 --> 00:47:22,135
do you know right now?

874
00:47:24,537 --> 00:47:25,438
At first,

875
00:47:26,806 --> 00:47:28,374
I thought I was trash
who betrayed my friend...

876
00:47:29,675 --> 00:47:32,145
and stole her boyfriend,

877
00:47:34,714 --> 00:47:36,649
but that happened...

878
00:47:37,416 --> 00:47:40,486
while I was trying to meet
Chairman Choi Young Ho for some reason.

879
00:47:42,655 --> 00:47:44,323
You know what that reason is, don't you?

880
00:47:45,057 --> 00:47:46,359
I'm warning you.

881
00:47:46,959 --> 00:47:48,361
Forget everything and live on.

882
00:47:49,629 --> 00:47:51,464
That's what's best for you.

883
00:47:52,698 --> 00:47:54,967
No, I need to know.

884
00:47:55,802 --> 00:47:58,504
Why I ended up stealing
my friend's boyfriend,

885
00:47:58,504 --> 00:48:00,907
and why I was trying to meet Chairman
Choi Young Ho, a man I didn't even know.

886
00:48:01,440 --> 00:48:03,776
Your old self is starting to come back.

887
00:48:06,345 --> 00:48:08,981
That vicious look
from when you came at me with this knife,

888
00:48:09,782 --> 00:48:11,484
saying you'd kill me.

889
00:48:12,118 --> 00:48:13,052
I...

890
00:48:14,554 --> 00:48:15,922
did that to you?

891
00:48:46,886 --> 00:48:48,754
That was when you were
in your third year of middle school.

892
00:48:49,555 --> 00:48:53,292
Your parents were always smiling,

893
00:48:55,027 --> 00:48:56,496
and they were deeply religious.

894
00:49:02,635 --> 00:49:04,337
The church...

895
00:49:05,538 --> 00:49:06,539
my mom and dad attended.

896
00:49:11,043 --> 00:49:12,411
From then on,

897
00:49:12,411 --> 00:49:14,547
everything started going wrong.

898
00:49:25,391 --> 00:49:26,559
There was an accident.

899
00:49:29,095 --> 00:49:30,196
Your family of three...

900
00:49:31,197 --> 00:49:33,132
lived in a greenhouse...

901
00:49:34,433 --> 00:49:35,935
because your father grew flowers.

902
00:49:38,070 --> 00:49:39,906
(Cheongham Farm)

903
00:49:41,941 --> 00:49:44,577
The day a fire broke out
and everything burned down,

904
00:49:45,244 --> 00:49:46,612
your parents died,

905
00:49:49,248 --> 00:49:50,883
and only you barely survived.

906
00:49:51,517 --> 00:49:53,186
What?

907
00:49:54,687 --> 00:49:55,922
The people in the neighborhood...

908
00:49:56,856 --> 00:49:58,391
hated me...

909
00:50:00,059 --> 00:50:01,394
saying I was just an unemployed bum,

910
00:50:02,528 --> 00:50:04,964
but your parents were the only ones
who were different.

911
00:50:05,798 --> 00:50:07,600
They treated me like a human being.

912
00:50:08,267 --> 00:50:09,469
- What are you saying?
- You...

913
00:50:10,536 --> 00:50:12,038
were polite,

914
00:50:13,639 --> 00:50:15,675
and a good student too.

915
00:50:17,109 --> 00:50:18,277
That was when it hit me.

916
00:50:20,346 --> 00:50:22,048
By the time I came to my senses,

917
00:50:23,149 --> 00:50:24,650
everything was already over.

918
00:50:24,650 --> 00:50:25,451
What...

919
00:50:26,185 --> 00:50:27,420
are you talking about right now?

920
00:50:27,420 --> 00:50:28,454
Just listen.

921
00:50:30,022 --> 00:50:31,157
There's a reason.

922
00:50:31,924 --> 00:50:34,360
(15 years ago)

923
00:50:34,360 --> 00:50:36,863
You killed those good people for money?

924
00:50:37,230 --> 00:50:39,065
You bastard.

925
00:50:39,065 --> 00:50:40,800
They were people who lived honestly.

926
00:50:41,400 --> 00:50:42,502
Why would you kill them?

927
00:50:42,502 --> 00:50:44,237
And you still call yourself human?

928
00:50:44,237 --> 00:50:46,806
You die too, you beast.

929
00:50:46,806 --> 00:50:48,841
Die!

930
00:50:48,841 --> 00:50:50,309
Goodness.

931
00:50:54,013 --> 00:50:55,648
You bastard.

932
00:50:56,482 --> 00:50:57,650
You evil bastard.

933
00:50:58,751 --> 00:50:59,952
That damned bastard.

934
00:51:04,390 --> 00:51:05,491
Myo Jin!

935
00:51:06,926 --> 00:51:07,793
Die.

936
00:51:08,060 --> 00:51:09,829
- Myo Jin, don't.
- Die!

937
00:51:12,165 --> 00:51:13,399
You die too!

938
00:51:13,800 --> 00:51:16,269
Let go of me! I'm going to kill him!

939
00:51:16,269 --> 00:51:17,670
I'm going to kill him!

940
00:51:17,670 --> 00:51:18,604
Hey!

941
00:51:24,844 --> 00:51:27,213
Where are you taking her right now?

942
00:51:27,213 --> 00:51:28,948
The suspect is injured,
so they both need to come with us first.

943
00:51:28,948 --> 00:51:29,782
Move aside.

944
00:51:29,782 --> 00:51:31,984
Her mother and father died overnight.

945
00:51:31,984 --> 00:51:33,886
How could she be in her right mind?

946
00:51:33,886 --> 00:51:35,488
Don't you feel sorry for the poor child?

947
00:51:35,888 --> 00:51:37,490
So what if you're a cop?

948
00:51:37,490 --> 00:51:38,891
I can't stand watching this.

949
00:51:40,326 --> 00:51:41,394
Let go.

950
00:51:41,394 --> 00:51:42,428
Go!

951
00:51:42,428 --> 00:51:44,397
Myo Jin, it's okay.

952
00:51:49,802 --> 00:51:50,970
It's okay.

953
00:51:51,804 --> 00:51:53,539
- Where are you going?
- Myo Jin, what is it all of a sudden?

954
00:52:03,149 --> 00:52:04,083
It's okay.

955
00:52:05,751 --> 00:52:06,586
Myo Jin.

956
00:52:32,645 --> 00:52:33,513
This...

957
00:52:34,747 --> 00:52:37,216
is the gift you gave me that day.

958
00:52:37,216 --> 00:52:38,284
You...

959
00:52:40,253 --> 00:52:42,221
killed my mom and dad?

960
00:52:42,455 --> 00:52:44,790
That's how I ended up going to prison,

961
00:52:47,460 --> 00:52:49,362
and I heard...

962
00:52:49,362 --> 00:52:51,264
the church your parents attended
took you in.

963
00:52:52,098 --> 00:52:54,066
I wanted to tell you the truth,

964
00:52:54,934 --> 00:52:57,770
but I thought
one tragedy ought to be enough.

965
00:52:59,005 --> 00:53:00,506
I prayed in prison...

966
00:53:01,607 --> 00:53:03,109
that you would forget all of this,

967
00:53:04,143 --> 00:53:05,411
and live a new life,

968
00:53:07,246 --> 00:53:09,048
that you'd be freed...

969
00:53:10,383 --> 00:53:11,551
from this hellish reality.

970
00:53:12,018 --> 00:53:13,219
What are you saying?

971
00:53:13,219 --> 00:53:14,821
But it was useless.

972
00:53:17,190 --> 00:53:19,826
It's been a little over two years now...

973
00:53:20,393 --> 00:53:22,195
because it was right after
I got out of prison.

974
00:53:27,233 --> 00:53:29,168
You came holding that knife,

975
00:53:31,003 --> 00:53:32,104
saying you'd kill me...

976
00:53:33,606 --> 00:53:35,608
and avenge your parents.

977
00:53:37,343 --> 00:53:38,244
Stop.

978
00:53:38,978 --> 00:53:40,346
You were such a good kid,

979
00:53:41,881 --> 00:53:44,083
but you'd turned into a complete monster.

980
00:53:46,486 --> 00:53:47,787
You must've been furious too...

981
00:53:49,121 --> 00:53:50,890
because you became an orphan overnight.

982
00:53:50,890 --> 00:53:52,458
- Please stop!
- I can tell...

983
00:53:53,426 --> 00:53:55,027
just by looking into someone's eyes...

984
00:53:57,029 --> 00:54:00,666
whether they really can
kill someone or not.

985
00:54:01,601 --> 00:54:02,568
And you...

986
00:54:03,503 --> 00:54:05,771
really looked like you could kill someone.

987
00:54:06,873 --> 00:54:09,041
Your desire to get revenge on me
turned you into a devil.

988
00:54:09,041 --> 00:54:09,876
Shut up.

989
00:54:10,476 --> 00:54:11,911
Please, shut up!

990
00:54:11,911 --> 00:54:13,713
Be quiet and listen to the end.

991
00:54:14,514 --> 00:54:16,482
I haven't even started yet.

992
00:54:21,287 --> 00:54:23,122
I don't need anything else.
Just tell me...

993
00:54:23,556 --> 00:54:25,558
whether you killed my mom and dad.

994
00:54:28,127 --> 00:54:29,061
Myo Jin!

995
00:54:30,863 --> 00:54:32,198
Do you miss your parents?

996
00:54:32,732 --> 00:54:34,734
Do you need to see blood
before you'll be satisfied?

997
00:54:35,201 --> 00:54:36,636
If you want revenge,

998
00:54:37,036 --> 00:54:38,905
get your head on straight first.

999
00:54:43,843 --> 00:54:45,545
Don't talk nonsense!

1000
00:54:45,545 --> 00:54:48,181
Hey, you tailed Ham Myo Jin
behind my back, didn't you?

1001
00:54:48,181 --> 00:54:50,616
You thought there'd be money in it,
so you wanted it all for yourself?

1002
00:54:50,950 --> 00:54:52,151
Have you lost your mind?

1003
00:54:52,151 --> 00:54:53,386
No.

1004
00:54:53,386 --> 00:54:56,556
It just kind of ended up that way.

1005
00:54:58,090 --> 00:55:00,693
Hey, if you keep this up,
there'll be nothing left for you.

1006
00:55:00,927 --> 00:55:02,995
Hey, what about Ryu Jun Ho?

1007
00:55:03,463 --> 00:55:05,798
He doesn't know a damn thing,

1008
00:55:05,798 --> 00:55:06,833
so you just worry about your side.

1009
00:55:06,833 --> 00:55:08,501
Okay, I'll call after I finish.

1010
00:55:10,536 --> 00:55:12,271
That's it. Let's go.

1011
00:55:13,239 --> 00:55:14,140
Young Gu.

1012
00:55:14,540 --> 00:55:15,541
Get them ready.

1013
00:55:15,541 --> 00:55:16,609
Yes, boss.

1014
00:55:17,443 --> 00:55:18,277
Ready!

1015
00:55:18,277 --> 00:55:19,212
Ready.

1016
00:55:29,589 --> 00:55:30,456
What's that?

1017
00:55:33,960 --> 00:55:34,827
What?

1018
00:55:35,194 --> 00:55:36,362
What do you mean, all of a sudden?

1019
00:55:36,662 --> 00:55:37,730
Can you see who it is?

1020
00:55:38,097 --> 00:55:40,266
The windows are blacked out.
I can't see anything inside.

1021
00:55:41,033 --> 00:55:42,835
There's someone else besides us...

1022
00:55:42,835 --> 00:55:44,303
who's after Ham Myo Jin?

1023
00:55:44,303 --> 00:55:45,538
Hey, forget it.

1024
00:55:45,538 --> 00:55:46,772
We're ignoring it and going in.

1025
00:55:47,240 --> 00:55:48,307
We won't get a chance like this again.

1026
00:55:48,307 --> 00:55:50,643
Don't be insane.
Are you trying to get yourself killed?

1027
00:55:50,643 --> 00:55:52,478
Stop talking shit and pull out now.

1028
00:55:52,478 --> 00:55:53,746
There are still businesses open here.

1029
00:55:53,746 --> 00:55:54,981
It must be somebody from one of them.

1030
00:55:54,981 --> 00:55:56,682
What are you scared of?

1031
00:55:56,682 --> 00:55:59,051
Don't make me repeat myself.

1032
00:55:59,051 --> 00:56:00,386
Pull out now.

1033
00:56:00,386 --> 00:56:03,055
If you don't,
you and I are done as of today.

1034
00:56:04,423 --> 00:56:05,825
Hey, you...

1035
00:56:05,825 --> 00:56:06,659
Hello?

1036
00:56:06,893 --> 00:56:09,595
This rude bitch
has really pushed it too far.

1037
00:56:09,595 --> 00:56:10,530
Hey, everybody out.

1038
00:56:15,501 --> 00:56:16,869
This is easy.

1039
00:56:16,869 --> 00:56:18,104
That woman from the photo
I showed you earlier.

1040
00:56:18,104 --> 00:56:20,106
The second you grab her, get her out fast.

1041
00:56:20,339 --> 00:56:21,707
Yes, boss.

1042
00:56:21,707 --> 00:56:22,542
Let's go.

1043
00:56:25,912 --> 00:56:28,114
(We're struggling enough just to get by,
so why talk about redevelopment?)

1044
00:56:28,114 --> 00:56:30,650
(Absolutely against
reckless redevelopment)

1045
00:56:33,452 --> 00:56:34,587
Hey, is this the place?

1046
00:56:34,987 --> 00:56:36,622
There isn't even a rat in sight.

1047
00:56:37,156 --> 00:56:39,025
This is the latest model,
so I'm sure of it.

1048
00:56:40,560 --> 00:56:41,794
Hey, stop the car.

1049
00:56:42,228 --> 00:56:43,329
I think there are people here.

1050
00:56:58,544 --> 00:57:00,680
Yeah, that's the car Mr. An's goons use.

1051
00:57:02,248 --> 00:57:03,149
What do you mean?

1052
00:57:03,683 --> 00:57:05,685
Whenever I drugged the drinks
and made the customers lose it,

1053
00:57:06,118 --> 00:57:07,920
Mr. An's goons would come.

1054
00:57:07,920 --> 00:57:10,223
And they always
hauled them off in that car.

1055
00:57:10,223 --> 00:57:12,458
It's nice seeing those bastards here.

1056
00:57:13,926 --> 00:57:14,727
What?

1057
00:57:15,127 --> 00:57:16,562
Look at you, idiot.

1058
00:57:35,548 --> 00:57:37,083
How'd you get your hands on that?

1059
00:57:37,083 --> 00:57:39,352
I got it from a vet.

1060
00:57:45,391 --> 00:57:46,592
Do we just leave him there?

1061
00:57:48,060 --> 00:57:49,128
He'll be fine.

1062
00:57:50,563 --> 00:57:51,597
Let's make this quick.

1063
00:57:57,770 --> 00:57:58,805
But...

1064
00:57:58,805 --> 00:58:01,107
do you know
what this Mr. An guy looks like?

1065
00:58:01,107 --> 00:58:02,675
How would I?

1066
00:58:02,675 --> 00:58:03,810
Have you seen him, boss?

1067
00:58:09,816 --> 00:58:12,185
You put that punk to sleep
without even knowing what he looks like?

1068
00:58:17,824 --> 00:58:18,925
Wake him back up.

1069
00:58:19,358 --> 00:58:21,661
Maybe I should kill you today,
you blockheaded bastard.

1070
00:58:21,661 --> 00:58:22,562
I'm sorry.

1071
00:58:22,562 --> 00:58:24,096
I'll wake him up right away.

1072
00:58:29,001 --> 00:58:30,436
Wake up, you fat bastard.

1073
00:58:32,271 --> 00:58:33,306
I'm sleepy.

1074
00:58:33,306 --> 00:58:34,607
My ass you are.

1075
00:58:34,607 --> 00:58:35,942
If you don't get up, I'll kill you.

1076
00:58:40,546 --> 00:58:41,447
What?

1077
00:58:53,693 --> 00:58:54,994
What's that now?

1078
00:59:32,031 --> 00:59:36,469
(REVERSE)

1079
00:59:36,669 --> 00:59:38,571
If she went out anyway,
you should've followed her,

1080
00:59:38,571 --> 00:59:40,206
or at least known where she was going.

1081
00:59:40,206 --> 00:59:41,774
They're not easy people,

1082
00:59:41,774 --> 00:59:43,776
so things could get ugly.

1083
00:59:43,776 --> 00:59:45,111
Don't stop.

1084
00:59:45,111 --> 00:59:47,480
What if they end up dead?

1085
00:59:47,480 --> 00:59:49,115
This isn't what I used to take.

1086
00:59:49,115 --> 00:59:51,017
Jun Ho said the hospital changed
your medication.

1087
00:59:51,017 --> 00:59:52,985
Do I really need that?

1088
00:59:53,252 --> 00:59:54,287
The two of them are working together,

1089
00:59:54,287 --> 00:59:55,822
trying to get rid of that woman.

1090
00:59:55,822 --> 00:59:56,956
Where's your boss?

1091
